      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAMEL PLUS (2) was a nose away in second at Central Wheatbelt over 2130m last start at his first run back from a spell. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Stepping up a level this time but he is fitter for that last hit-out and is capable of making his presence felt. PAPPINBARRA LADY (10) has been competitive of late and kept the ball rolling last time when 5 metres from the winner in fifth over 1730m at Gloucester Park. Draws out a little on the second line and may need luck at some point. Meets a similar line up and she is a strong winning hope. CHEVRONS GOLD (6) is heading the right way, improving last time out to finish third at Central Wheatbelt over 2130m. Genuine top-three threat. PURELY PANDEMIC (3) is worth another chance after a last-start seventh over 1730m at Gloucester Park four days ago. This is an easier assignment.",
